files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.EvaluateOverheadAttribute
files.Summary: Specifies if the overhead should be evaluated (Idle runs) and it's average value subtracted from every result. True by default, very important for nano-benchmarks.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.GcConcurrentAttribute
files.Summary: Specifies whether the common language runtime runs garbage collection on a separate thread. false: Does not run garbage collection concurrently. true: Runs garbage collection concurrently. This is the default.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.GcForceAttribute
files.Summary: Specifies whether the BenchmarkDotNet's benchmark runner forces full garbage collection after each benchmark invocation false: Does not force garbage collection. true: Forces full garbage collection after each benchmark invocation. This is the default.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.GcServerAttribute
files.Summary: Specifies whether the common language runtime runs server garbage collection. false: Does not run server garbage collection. This is the default. true: Runs server garbage collection.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.GlobalCleanupAttribute
files.Summary: Marks method to be executed after all benchmark iterations. It's going to be executed only once, after all benchmark runs.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.GlobalSetupAttribute
files.Summary: Marks method to be executed before all benchmark iterations. It's going to be executed only once, just before warm up.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.InnerIterationCountAttribute
files.Summary: Invocation count in a single iteration. Does exactly the same as InvocationCountAttribute, added to make porting from xunit-performance to BenchmarkDotNet easier

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.InvocationCountAttribute
files.Summary: Invocation count in a single iteration. If specified, will be ignored. If specified, it must be a multiple of .

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.IterationCleanupAttribute
files.Summary: Marks method to be executed after each benchmark iteration. This should NOT be used for microbenchmarks - please see the docs.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.IterationCountAttribute
files.Summary: How many target iterations should be performed If specified, will be ignored. If specified, will be ignored.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.IterationSetupAttribute
files.Summary: Marks method to be executed before each benchmark iteration. This should NOT be used for microbenchmarks - please see the docs.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.IterationTimeAttribute
files.Summary: Desired time of execution of an iteration. Used by Pilot stage to estimate the number of invocations per iteration. The default value is 500 milliseconds.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.KeepBenchmarkFilesAttribute
files.Summary: determines if all auto-generated files should be kept or removed after running the benchmarks

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.MaxAbsoluteErrorAttribute
files.Summary: Maximum acceptable error for a benchmark (by default, BenchmarkDotNet continue iterations until the actual error is less than the specified error). Doesn't have a default value. If is also provided, the smallest value is used as stop criteria.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.MaxIterationCountAttribute
files.Summary: Maximum count of target iterations that should be performed The default value is 100 If you set this value to below 15, then is not going to work

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.MaxRelativeErrorAttribute
files.Summary: Maximum acceptable error for a benchmark (by default, BenchmarkDotNet continue iterations until the actual error is less than the specified error). The default value is 0.02. If is also provided, the smallest value is used as stop criteria.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.MaxWarmupCountAttribute
files.Summary: Maximum count of warmup iterations that should be performed The default value is 50

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.MemoryRandomizationAttribute
files.Summary: specifies whether Engine should allocate some random-sized memory between iterations it makes [GlobalCleanup] and [GlobalSetup] methods to be executed after every iteration

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.MinInvokeCountAttribute
files.Summary: Minimum count of benchmark invocations per iteration. The default value is 4.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.MinIterationCountAttribute
files.Summary: Minimum count of target iterations that should be performed. The default value is 15. If you set this value to below 15, then is not going to work.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.MinIterationTimeAttribute
files.Summary: Minimum time of a single iteration. Unlike Run.IterationTime, this characteristic specifies only the lower limit. In case of need, BenchmarkDotNet can increase this value. The default value is 500 milliseconds.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.MinWarmupCountAttribute
files.Summary: Minimum count of warmup iterations that should be performed The default value is 6

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.MValueColumnAttribute
files.Summary: Prints mvalue. See http://www.brendangregg.com/FrequencyTrails/modes.html

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.NamespaceColumnAttribute
files.Summary: Add a column with the target method namespace.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.OutliersAttribute
files.Summary: Specifies which outliers should be removed from the distribution

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.ProcessCountAttribute
files.Summary: How many times we should launch process with target benchmark.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.RunOncePerIterationAttribute
files.Summary: Run the benchmark exactly once per iteration.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.StopOnFirstErrorAttribute
files.Summary: determines if running should be stop after first error

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.TargetedAttribute
files.Summary: Base class for attributes that are targeted at one or more method(s)

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.UnicodeConsoleLoggerAttribute
files.Summary: Enable unicode support in console logger

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.WakeLockAttribute
files.Summary: Placing a on your assembly or class controls whether the Windows system enters sleep or turns off the display while benchmarks run.

files.Title: BenchmarkDotNet.Attributes.WarmupCountAttribute
files.Summary: How many warmup iterations should be performed.
